msItem.title: A compendium of the Hebrew Bible analysing biblical verses (from Psalms, Genesis, Exodus)

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 2; ruled lines: 15; written lines: 15; Uniform layout. Text only on recto sides, verso sides are left blank. Ruling is visible. Printer's waste as back pastedown.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Enlgish cursive and Hebrew square script of the 18th century.

binding.p: Parchment binding; title on the front cover: 'תהלים עברים בדל The Hebrew Psalms analized. William Button Aug. 25 1766.' Spine: 'Brit. Mus. Or. 9903. W. Button. Psalms Analized, &c. Hebrew & English.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: Moses Gaster (b. 1856, d. 1939), scholar and rabbi: his manuscript, Cod. G. 455: inscribed with his name (folio 1r); purchased by the British Museum from him on 12 April, 1924: inscribed (back flyleaf [i]r).
